    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3347429627" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3347429627" />
    <a title="Joshua French" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/93387837-joshua-french"><img alt="Joshua French" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3347429627?book_show_action=true">May 20, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Joshua French" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Joshua French" href="/user/show/93387837-joshua-french">Joshua French</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3347429627" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16409673977417679067">A delightfully well-plotted and beautifully written novel!<br/><br/>Clementina and Vince have very little in common except wounds from their time serving as nurse and soldier on the front World War I, some wounds visible and some not. The story follows their chance meeting after the war (in 1920) and the dramatic and unexpected changes this will make to both their lives. The novel is easy to read while also beautifully poetic (‘Champagne and glasses and a stack of toasts, thin and crisp as autumn leaves’)</span>
  <span id="freeText16409673977417679067" style="display:none">A delightfully well-plotted and beautifully written novel!<br /><br />Clementina and Vince have very little in common except wounds from their time serving as nurse and soldier on the front World War I, some wounds visible and some not. The story follows their chance meeting after the war (in 1920) and the dramatic and unexpected changes this will make to both their lives. The novel is easy to read while also beautifully poetic (‘Champagne and glasses and a stack of toasts, thin and crisp as autumn leaves’), the characters vivid and entertaining - the pub landlady Doll was a highlight - and the plot is fast-paced and unpredictable. I haven’t enjoyed a novel this much in ages…. (or has a novel made me cry as much!). <br /><br />Very much recommended. Another enjoyable gem from the underrated Lesley Glaister...</span>
  <a data-text-id="16409673977417679067" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


