<div id="review_4240922444" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4240922444" />
    <a title="Livy" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/101171792-livy"><img alt="Livy" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1629991844p2/101171792.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4240922444?book_show_action=true">Sep 16, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Livy" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Livy" href="/user/show/101171792-livy">Livy</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781913207922" href="/book/show/58735108-blasted-things">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4240922444" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5616874581032278899">This book was a well-written and clearly well-researched book centered around a woman who has suffered some very traumatic losses and has to deal with them and try and live her life within the confines of society.<br/><br/>Clem was an interesting character who meant well but just ended up in some situations that weren&apos;t right for her, especially seeing what happened at the start of the book and everything that she went through then. Harri and Gwen were great supports for them and I loved how their charact</span>
  <span id="freeText5616874581032278899" style="display:none">This book was a well-written and clearly well-researched book centered around a woman who has suffered some very traumatic losses and has to deal with them and try and live her life within the confines of society.<br /><br />Clem was an interesting character who meant well but just ended up in some situations that weren't right for her, especially seeing what happened at the start of the book and everything that she went through then. Harri and Gwen were great supports for them and I loved how their character arcs ended, as it was a bit of a surprise but in a good way. The characters that I did not like were Dennis and Vincent. The way they both treated Clem was shocking and their misogyny (albeit in keeping with the time period of the book) just really rubbed me up the wrong way, which definitely detracted from my enjoyment of the book. <br /><br />The plot itself was incredibly interesting and I did like how it turned out after the dramatic beginning, even if it was not quite the direction that I thought it was going to go on based on the summary. It was dramatic and had some darker moments and some sadder moments. It was a well-crafted story that I did really enjoy reading, however, I think that it just wasn't all up my alley and I didn't like certain elements of the story as they just didn't sit quite right with me. </span>
  <a data-text-id="5616874581032278899" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


